News updates on Six Flags World of Owl City theme park at the Six Flags Owatonna Resort: Owl City just dropped a teaser for the new single, "Car Trouble", releasing on March 1st, 2024, as new rumors suggesting that the prototype RMC Mine Train Coaster would be no longer based on 'Grapefruit' but instead Adam Young and Six Flags are in talks with Kinema Citrus for theme park licensing rights for a new area of the park based on the TV anime series, The Rising of the Shield Hero. It will be the first fully-themed anime theme park area in North America once its fully constructed and opened to the general public for the 2026 season at the earliest. Once Owl City announces their eighth studio album in the near future, the area will be fully retheme to the latest album plus references to the lyrics from the songs plus rides and attractions (except for The Rising of the Shield Hero themed RMC Mine Train Coaster) will be renamed as well. Six Flags World of Owl City will have enough IPs they have owned to avoid an IP Clash in order to compete with Disney and Universal

  • Vinland Saga
  • Bocchi the Rock!
  • Attack on Titan
  • Neural Cloud
  • Vocaloid/Hatsune Miku
  • Ochi No Ko
  • The Rising of the Shield Hero The list of IPs owned by Six Flags have been granted to use by the park:
  • Looney Tunes

Robdeltonie 2024-02-21 5:43 AM
I just came across a video explaining Floppy Fish for those not in the know. https://youtu.be/ow3huk-efk4 However, it posits the theory that the Discord server spamming "Release Floppy Fish" on Adam's Instagram on January 31st made Adam decide to revisit the song and release it as the new single Car Trouble. I hate to be that guy and burst everyone's bubble, but I don't think that's true. While it's a nice theory, when Adam first announced Coco Moon Deluxe and teased his cover of Boston on Instagram, he also showed the tracklisting and release dates, which included the release of Car Trouble on March 1st. That post was made on January 25th, almost a week before this Discord server started spamming Adam en masse. So, unless there's another song called Car Trouble that Adam decided to scrap to release Floppy Fish in its spot with the same title, I don't think this Discord's spamming influenced Adam's decision to make this happen. That's not to say that fans had no role in doing so. In fact, if anyone had any recent impact on that decision, it's /u/lunarhoneymoon on Reddit (don't know if they're here on Discord), who went to a concert with a sign that said, "Release Floppy Fish (please)", which Adam pointed to during the concert. I know this wall of text won't be popular for pointing this out, but it's the unfortunate truth. With that said, we should all be glad that Adam chose to release it at all. Here's to an exciting March 1st!!
